correctness.rationale: Multiple critical inaccuracies and non-traceable values are present despite some correct elements (PEALD method, precursors/co-reactant, plasma power 1200 W, pressure ~9 Torr, substrate, 10 nm film, and TFT metrics). Key issues: (1) Dosing/purge times are wrong by 10^3 due to unit misuse: article reports seconds (DADI 0.5 s, TMGa 0.5 s, DEZ 0.1 s, plasma 12 s; purges 8 s), but extraction encodes Millisecond units with the same numeric values (0.5, 0.1, 12, 8 ms). Should be 500 ms, 100 ms, 12000 ms, and 8000 ms. (2) Deposition temperature 200 °C is not reported in the article (fabricated). (3) Flow rates (precursor/co-reactant/purge), growth-per-cycle values (0.1 Å), number of cycles (100), nucleation period (5 cycles), uniformity (3.5%), conformality (AR 10), optical properties (n, absorption, band gap), film electrical properties (resistivity, carrier density, Hall mobility and method), roughness (0.8 nm), and density (5.2 g/dm^3) are all absent from the paper and thus untraceable/fabricated. (4) Subthreshold swing is mis-encoded: article gives 0.53 V/dec; schema requires MilliV, so it should be 530 mV, not 0.53 mV. (5) ElementalConcentration is improperly represented as a single 33.3% value and is not supported by the paper; only the atomic ratio 1:1:1 is reported (via XPS). (6) SupercycleDesign with 1:1:1 subcycles is not explicitly given; the paper only states the best film atomic ratio is 1:1:1, not the n1:n2:n3 cycle counts. (7) Carrier and purging gases are set to Ar but not specified in the text (only Ar/O2 plasma is reported). (8) Internal inconsistency: GPC × cycles (0.1 Å × 100 = 1 nm) conflicts with the stated 10 nm film thickness. Corrections needed: fix time units to ms, correct SS to 530 mV, remove/avoid inventing unsupported parameters (temperature, flow rates, GPC, cycles, nucleation period, optical/electrical/structural metrics, uniformity/conformality, roughness, density, stability/reproducibility) or clearly mark as not reported per schema adaptation, and align composition reporting with the article (retain atomic ratio 1:1:1 determined by XPS).

completeness.rationale: Significant factual and schema-alignment issues and missing processes. Key problems: (1) Multiple reported compositions are not represented. The article presents several IGZO films/devices (In contents 10/30/60% and Ga contents 10/30/60%, plus the best 1:1:1 case). The extraction provides only one process, omitting distinct processes and their device metrics from Table 1. (2) Fabricated or untraceable parameters: deposition temperature (200 °C), growth-per-cycle, number of cycles, nucleation period, saturation flag, all flow rates, reactor manufacturer, supercycle subcycle counts, uniformity, conformality, roughness, density, refractive index, absorption, band gap, resistivity, carrier density, Hall method, XRD/AFM/XRR characterizations—none are reported in the article. (3) Unit errors: dosing and purge times are given in seconds in the article (0.5 s, 12 s, 8 s) but encoded as MilliSEC with values 0.5, 12.0, 8.0, off by 10^3; subthreshold swing is 0.53 V/dec in the article but encoded as 0.53 MilliV (should be 530 mV). (4) Supercycle design: counts of 1:1:1 are not supported by the text; only the atomic ratio 1:1:1 is reported. (5) Carrier/purging gas set to Ar is not explicitly stated (only Ar/O2 plasma is mentioned). Positives: precursors, co-reactant (Ar/O2 plasma), plasma power (1200 W), pressure (~9 Torr), substrate, film thickness (10 nm), and device structure are correctly captured. To improve: add separate processes for each composition studied with correct device metrics; correct all time and SS units; remove or revise all ungrounded values (GPC, cycles, flows, optical/structural/electrical film properties, characterization methods, supercycle counts) to match the article or omit if not reported; ensure carrier/purging gases are traceable if included.
